  "description": "Introduce a central YAML configuration file at `.orchestrator/config.yaml` and a Python config module (`config.py`) that loads it, replacing the hardcoded constants scattered across runner.py, cli.py, skills.py, scheduler.py, and prompts.py. This phase creates the config infrastructure with frozen dataclasses, a YAML loader with missing-file fallback, and per-agent-type tool allowlisting for Claude Code. Subsequent phases wire the config into existing modules.",
